MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Two interlocking renderer-side bugs cause every transparent region in
indexed (8bpp) mode to render as solid magenta (CRITICAL visual
regression vs kill-switch baseline):

1. paletteRemapFor() lookup mismatch — the palmap cache is keyed by
   relative paths ("Title.pbm") per the format spec, but every
   callsite passes ResourceManager::getPath() output ("data/Title.pbm").
   Every lookup missed and every sprite fell through to the truecolor
   slow path.

2. SDL_ConvertSurface alpha-bake side-effect — _remap_truecolor_to_master
   called SDL_ConvertSurface(src, RGBA32) on a colorkeyed surface; SDL3
   invokes SDL_ConvertColorkeyToAlpha when dst format has alpha
   (vendor/SDL/src/video/SDL_surface.c:2119), baking colorkeyed pixels
   to alpha=0. The remap then mapped alpha==0 → master 255 (magenta).
   loadImage afterward set the result colorkey to master 0 (black), so
   the now-magenta transparent pixels never matched the colorkey-skip
   test in _blit_indexed and were drawn as solid magenta.

Fixes: paletteRemapFor strips trailing "data/" component on lookup
miss; _remap_truecolor_to_master strips src colorkey at entry so
SDL_ConvertSurface preserves alpha=255 (the (0,0,0)→0 and
(255,0,255)→255 special cases in _nearest_master_index_local handle
both flavors of transparency via RGB matching alone). Adds a third
branch in loadImage for INDEX8 source without palmap entry (mod /
unknown asset) that builds a runtime LUT from the source palette
instead of routing through the truecolor path. Bounded diagnostic
(first 8 calls per boot) logs format/remap-status/path for future
regression detection.

Smoke validated on DOSBox-X stage build: title (curmap=72) and Cave
Story menu (curmap=1005) both match their kill-switch RGB565 baselines.

Independent of the parallel wave-16-1 corrigendum regenerating
master.palmap; renderer-side fix coexists with regenerated LUTs.
---
 src/graphics/Renderer.cpp | 51 +++++++++++++++++++++++++-
 src/graphics/Surface.cpp  | 77 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++-
 2 files changed, 125 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

diff --git a/src/graphics/Renderer.cpp b/src/graphics/Renderer.cpp
index d34fe70..78d3d62 100644
--- a/src/graphics/Renderer.cpp
+++ b/src/graphics/Renderer.cpp
@@ -1407,8 +1407,57 @@ truncated:
 
 const std::array<Uint8, 256>* Renderer::paletteRemapFor(const std::string &asset_name) const
 {
+  // Try a literal lookup first (matches the format spec §2.2 contract:
+  // palmap keys are "Title.pbm", "Npc/NpcGuest.pbm", relative to data/).
   auto it = _palmap_cache.find(asset_name);
-  return (it != _palmap_cache.end()) ? &it->second : nullptr;
+  if (it != _palmap_cache.end()) return &it->second;
+
+  // DOS-PORT (patch 0078, Phase 9 wave 16 hotfix): runtime callers go
+  // through ResourceManager::getPath which prepends "data/" (or an
+  // absolute path ending in "/data/"). Without this prefix-strip, every
+  // sprite load missed the palmap cache, fell through to the truecolor
+  // slow path, and that path alpha-flattens colorkey pixels in
+  // SDL_ConvertSurface to RGBA32 — turning source-(0,0,0) pixels into
+  // master 255 (magenta) via the alpha==0 special case. Then loadImage
+  // set colorkey=0 (master black) on the result, so the now-magenta
+  // pixels failed the colorkey test and were drawn — the wave-16
+  // "transparent regions render as solid magenta" regression.
+  //
+  // Strip everything up to and including the trailing "data/" component
+  // and retry. Both forward slashes and backslashes are accepted (the
+  // build tool emits forward, but DOS callsites can produce backslashes
+  // through path concatenation).
+  auto strip_to_relative = [](const std::string &p) -> std::string {
+    // Find the LAST "data/" or "data\" so an absolute path like
+    // "/home/user/data/Foo.pbm" reduces to "Foo.pbm" and a relative
+    // path like "data/Foo.pbm" does the same.
+    size_t best = std::string::npos;
+    for (size_t i = 0; i + 5 <= p.size(); ++i)
+    {
+      if ((p[i] == 'd' || p[i] == 'D') &&
+          (p[i + 1] == 'a' || p[i + 1] == 'A') &&
+          (p[i + 2] == 't' || p[i + 2] == 'T') &&
+          (p[i + 3] == 'a' || p[i + 3] == 'A') &&
+          (p[i + 4] == '/' || p[i + 4] == '\\'))
+      {
+        // Require the "data" component to be at the start, or preceded
+        // by a separator — guards against false matches inside a
+        // longer name like "metadata/foo".
+        if (i == 0 || p[i - 1] == '/' || p[i - 1] == '\\')
+          best = i + 5;
+      }
+    }
+    if (best != std::string::npos) return p.substr(best);
+    return std::string();
+  };
+
+  const std::string rel = strip_to_relative(asset_name);
+  if (!rel.empty())
+  {
+    it = _palmap_cache.find(rel);
+    if (it != _palmap_cache.end()) return &it->second;
+  }
+  return nullptr;
 }
 
 bool Renderer::flushAll()
diff --git a/src/graphics/Surface.cpp b/src/graphics/Surface.cpp
index 9bb5815..facc8d5 100644
--- a/src/graphics/Surface.cpp
+++ b/src/graphics/Surface.cpp
@@ -81,10 +81,32 @@ static SDL_Surface *_remap_indexed_to_master(SDL_Surface *src,
 // 320×240 truecolor background with ~1000 unique colors only does ~1000
 // nearest-color walks instead of 76800. For the 3 known truecolor
 // backgrounds at boot this is the difference between ~50 ms and ~3 s.
+//
+// DOS-PORT (patch 0078, Phase 9 wave 16 hotfix): MUTATES `src` —
+// strips its colorkey at function entry. Both call sites (loadImage
+// truecolor branch + loadFromSDLSurface INDEX8 branch) destroy `src`
+// immediately after the call, so the mutation is invisible to other
+// callers. The strip is required because the next line's
+// SDL_ConvertSurface(src, RGBA32) invokes SDL_ConvertColorkeyToAlpha
+// (vendor/SDL/src/video/SDL_surface.c:2119) on the result whenever the
+// source surface has SDL_COPY_COLORKEY set — that side-effect bakes
+// colorkeyed pixels into alpha=0, which then trips the alpha==0 →
+// master 255 (magenta) branch below. Pre-fix, transparent regions in
+// every sprite (`Title.pbm`, Cave Story logo, menu bezels, credits
+// text bg) landed at master 255 while loadImage set the result
+// colorkey to master 0, so _blit_indexed's `byte != 0` test never
+// skipped those pixels and they were drawn as solid magenta.
+//
+// Stripping the colorkey lets SDL_ConvertSurface preserve alpha=255
+// for every pixel; the (0,0,0)→0 and (255,0,255)→255 special cases in
+// _nearest_master_index_local then map both flavors of "transparent"
+// (sprite black, font magenta) to the right master index based on RGB
+// alone — independent of the colorkey-as-alpha mechanism.
 static SDL_Surface *_remap_truecolor_to_master(SDL_Surface *src,
                                                SDL_Palette *master_palette)
 {
   if (!src || !master_palette) return nullptr;
+  SDL_SetSurfaceColorKey(src, false, 0);  // see header comment for why.
   SDL_Surface *rgba = SDL_ConvertSurface(src, SDL_PIXELFORMAT_RGBA32);
   if (!rgba) return nullptr;
   SDL_Surface *dst = SDL_CreateSurface(src->w, src->h, SDL_PIXELFORMAT_INDEX8);
@@ -184,15 +206,66 @@ bool Surface::loadImage(const std::string &pbm_name, bool use_colorkey)
   {
     SDL_Surface *image_idx = nullptr;
     const std::array<Uint8, 256> *remap = r->paletteRemapFor(pbm_name);
+    // DOS-PORT (patch 0078, Phase 9 wave 16 hotfix): diagnostic for the
+    // wave-16 magenta-bleed root-cause investigation. Logs the first 8
+    // loads' palmap-hit status + chosen remap path so post-iter grep
+    // confirms the fix routes assets through the precomputed LUT
+    // instead of the alpha-flatten truecolor path. Bounded to 8 lines
+    // total so DEBUG.LOG isn't spammed on subsequent boots.
+    {
+      static int _palmap_diag_count = 0;
+      if (_palmap_diag_count < 8)
+      {
+        ++_palmap_diag_count;
+        const char *path =
+          (image_scaled->format == SDL_PIXELFORMAT_INDEX8 && remap) ? "indexed-LUT" :
+          (image_scaled->format == SDL_PIXELFORMAT_INDEX8) ? "indexed-no-LUT (slow truecolor fallback — BUG TRIGGER)" :
+          "truecolor";
+        LOG_INFO("Surface::loadImage palmap-diag #{}: '{}' fmt={} remap={} → path={}",
+                 _palmap_diag_count, pbm_name,
+                 SDL_GetPixelFormatName(image_scaled->format),
+                 remap ? "HIT" : "MISS", path);
+      }
+    }
     if (image_scaled->format == SDL_PIXELFORMAT_INDEX8 && remap)
     {
       image_idx = _remap_indexed_to_master(image_scaled, remap->data(),
                                            r->masterPalette());
     }
+    else if (image_scaled->format == SDL_PIXELFORMAT_INDEX8)
+    {
+      // DOS-PORT (patch 0078, Phase 9 wave 16 hotfix): INDEX8 source
+      // without a precomputed palmap entry (mod / unknown asset).
+      // Build a runtime LUT from the source palette directly — avoids
+      // the SDL_ConvertSurface→RGBA32→alpha-flatten path which loses the
+      // (0,0,0)→master-0 colorkey-stable rule when the source has a
+      // colorkey set. Pre-fix, this fell through to
+      // _remap_truecolor_to_master which produced master-255 (magenta)
+      // for every transparent source pixel, then loadImage set
+      // colorkey=0 (master black) on the result — the post-fix path
+      // routes through paletteRemapFor() above for stock assets, so
+      // this branch only fires for true mods.
+      Uint8 dyn_lut[256] = {0};
+      SDL_Palette *src_pal = SDL_GetSurfacePalette(image_scaled);
+      if (src_pal)
+      {
+        const SDL_Color *master_colors = r->masterPalette()->colors;
+        const int n = src_pal->ncolors;
+        for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i)
+        {
+          dyn_lut[i] = _nearest_master_index_local(master_colors,
+                                                   src_pal->colors[i].r,
+                                                   src_pal->colors[i].g,
+                                                   src_pal->colors[i].b);
+        }
+      }
+      image_idx = _remap_indexed_to_master(image_scaled, dyn_lut,
+                                           r->masterPalette());
+    }
     else
     {
-      // Truecolor source OR indexed source not in remap cache (mod /
-      // unknown asset). Slow per-pixel nearest-color path.
+      // Genuine truecolor source (32bpp bkHellsh.pbm / bkLight.pbm /
+      // bkSunset.pbm). Slow per-pixel nearest-color path.
       image_idx = _remap_truecolor_to_master(image_scaled, r->masterPalette());
     }
     SDL_DestroySurface(image_scaled);
